content: Just spent 2 hours optimizing the neural interface prototype. Early testing shows promising results in reducing decision-making time.
The AI trading algorithm hit 91% accuracy in today's simulation. Feels like we're on the cusp of something big.
Took a tech-free day. Went for a hike with friends, no phones. The mind feels clearer, and I've got some new ideas for the policy paper.
Scheduled a meeting with Dr. Li to finalize our policy paper. We'll discuss the integration of empathy in AI ethics.
Just got an email from the AI ethics conference. My proposal for a panel discussion on neural interfaces was accepted!
AI latency dropped to 16%. Still pushing for that 20% but each percentage point is a victory.
Had a setback with the neural interface prototype. Calibration issues. Back to the drawing board to refine the hardware setup.
Dr. Li and I agreed on the structure for our policy paper. We've got a solid outline now, next step: fleshing out the details.
Another tech-free day. Took the subway without my phone. Surprisingly, the world didn't end, and I had some great conversations.
The AI module now at 92% accuracy. We're fine-tuning the algorithms to get even more precise.
Got the neural interface prototype working smoothly after some hardware tweaks. Testing with actual trading data next week.
Dr. Li and I had a productive session. We're focusing on how AI can foster empathy in financial decision-making. Fascinating stuff.
AI's latency is now at 19%. One more push to hit our goal. The team's dedication is truly paying off.
Spent the day preparing for the AI ethics conference. Got my slides ready and a mock Q&A session with the team.
Just finished the first draft of the policy paper with Dr. Li. It's a nuanced look at AI ethics, and I'm proud of what we've accomplished.
